President Muhammadu Buhari has sent a message of condolence to the government and people of Kwara State on the passing away of Alhaji Usman Ndalolo, Waziri Patigi. The Presidentâ€™s message was contained in a statement issued by his Senior Special Assistant on Media and Publicity, Mallam Garba Shehu. In the message, the President stated that the late Ndalolo, a retired orthopaedic technician and community leader, who died at the age of 83, was a visionary statesman with impeccable integrity and dedication. The president said the late monarch will be remembered for his sagacity and exemplary selfless service to the people of Nigeria. Buhari paid respects to the late Usman Ndalolo and extended sympathies to the bereaved wife, Hajiya Amina Ndalolo, a former Minister of State, Health, family members, and the government and people of Kwara State. He prayed to Almighty Allah to repose his soul.